Exercise 6¶

  • given the following un-normalized posterior distribution $$ g(\theta |x) \propto \frac{1}{2} \exp{\bigg[-\frac{(\theta + 3)^2}{2}\bigg]} + \frac{1}{2} \exp{\bigg[-\frac{(\theta - 3)^2}{2}\bigg]} $$

  • draw a Markov Chain from the posterior distribution using a Metropolis-Hastings algorithm

  • use a Norm (0, 1) as random-walk candidate density

In [ ]:
# define posterior
test_posterior <- function(theta){
    g <- 0.5 * exp(-(theta+3)^2/2) + 0.5 * exp(-(theta-3)^2/2)
    return(g)
}

theta <- seq(-10, 10, 0.001)
In [ ]:
# write the metropolis algorithm
metropolis <- function(func, theta.i, n.samples, burn.in){
    theta.now <- theta.i
    func.now <- func(theta.now)
    n <- n.samples + burn.in

    # matrix to see the evolution of the chian
    samples <- matrix(data = NA, nrow = n, ncol = 2)

    # counter
    accepted <- 0

    for(i in 1:n){
        theta.prop <- rnorm(1, theta.now, 1)
        func.prop <- func(theta.prop)
        rho <- func.prop / func.now

        if(rho >= 1 || rho >= runif(1)){
            theta.now <- theta.prop
            func.now <- func.prop
            accepted <- accepted + 1
        }

        samples[i, 1] <- func.now
        samples[i, 2] <- theta.now
    }
    rate <- accepted / n
    print(rate)
    return(samples)
}
In [ ]:
# running parameters
theta.i <- 0
n.samples <- 10e5
In [ ]:
# run the chain
set.seed(010623)
chain <- metropolis(test_posterior, theta.i, n.samples, 0)

# normalize the test posterior
norm_test_posterior <- test_posterior(theta) / integrate(function(theta) test_posterior(theta), -10, 10)$value

# plot

  • try to use different burn-in cycles and thinning and plot the corresponding posterior distribution and the chain autocorrelation function. What are the best parameters ?
In [ ]:
burn.in <- c(100, 400, 700, 1000)
thin <- c(2, 10, 20, 30)
In [ ]:
# plot options
options(repr.plot.width = 16, repr.plot.height = 16)
par(mfrow = c(4,2), oma = c(0, 0, 0, 0))
colors = c('red', 'green3', 'blue', 'orange')

new_lags <- seq(0, 500, 5)

for(j in 1:4){
    new_chain <- metropolis(test_posterior, theta.i , n.samples, burn.in[j])

    # thinning the chain
    thin_chain <- new_chain[seq(1, nrow(new_chain), by = thin[j]), ]

    # define the density
    thin_postden <- density(thin_chain[, 2], n = 2^10)

    # analize with CODA
    thin_coda_chain <- as.mcmc(thin_chain[, 2])
    thin_ACF <- autocorr(thin_coda_chain, lags = new_lags)
    eff_size <- effectiveSize(thin_coda_chain)

    plot(thin_postden$x, thin_postden$y,
        type = 'l', lwd = 2,
        col = colors[j],
        xlab = expression(paste(theta)), ylab = 'MCMC posterior',
        main = paste("Burn-in = ", burn.in[j], ", thinning = ", thin[j]))
    grid(nx = NULL, ny = NULL,
	    lty = 2, lwd = 0.5,
	    col = 'gray')
    plot(new_lags, thin_ACF,
        pch = 19, col = colors[j],
        ylab = 'ACF')
    grid(nx = NULL, ny = NULL,
	    lty = 2, lwd = 0.5,
	    col = 'gray')
}
